1.Files
------------------------------------------------------------------
README		this file
Makefile	a makefile to build the example
run.sh		a shell script to run compiler with the specified 
------------------------------------------------------------------
p3		revised p3 experiment
config		directory to store grammar files
  |--c0.lex, c0.y	
  |             grammar files of c0 language
src		directory to store source files 
  |--c0.lex.c   lexer file generated by flex from ../config/c0.lex
  |--c0.tab.c   parser file generated by Bison from ../config/c0.y 
  |--c0.tab.h	header file generated by Bison from ../config/c0.y
test		directory to store test files
  |		c0 test programs
	--1.in
	--2.in
	--3.in
	--4.in
	--5.in
  |		pl0 test programs
	--test1.pl0
	--test2.pl0
	--test3.pl0
	--test4.pl0
	--test5.pl0
doc
  |--bison.example分析.pdf	
		document that analyse bison.example
  |--AST.pdf
		document that analyse AST
bin		directory to store executable files
------------------------------------------------------------------

2.Building c/0 parser 
   $ make
or
   $ make c0
   ...

(Clean c/0 compiler)
   $ make clean

3.Run a parser to parse a program.
  $ ./run.sh c0 1.in
  It is the same as the commandline "bin/c0 <test/1.in".

------------------------------------------------------------------

4.About this experiment
  This experiment is pretty simple as we get the bison.example to follow and we already wrote a co grammar.But I had a hard time with the conflicts in c0.y.Finally,p4 is Complished as the teacher required.  

